headline: JP Morgan Keeps Neutral Rating on Target (TGT), Lifts PT
summary: On May 22, JPMorgan analyst Christopher Horvers raised the firm’s price target on Target Corp. (NYSE:TGT) to $109 from $105 and kept a Neutral rating on the stock. headline: The S&P 500 Is Up 13% in 1 Month, but These 2 High-Yield Dividend Stocks and ETF Are Still Too Cheap to Ignore
summary: NextEra Energy has steadily powered its dividend higher for more than 30 consecutive years, and it doesn't expect to stop doing so anytime soon.  Target’s results continue to disappoint, but the stock is incredibly cheap.  The JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF can be counted on to provide reliable monthly income, even in a downturn.

headline: Target's Market Share Is Slipping -- Time to Buy the Dip or Stay Away?
summary: Target has been losing market share to its retail rivals.  Meanwhile, it just reported poor Q1 results and lowered its full-year guidance.  While its stock managed to rise following its fiscal first-quarter earnings report last week, there was not much to cheer about with Target's (NYSE: TGT) latest results.
